The paper deals with image manipulation and generation, specifically object transfiguration and attribute subspace learning. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of adversarial training and generative models also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The spatial alignment of images and use of landmarks suggests the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the use of datasets and image generation suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
